import { Component, ElementRef, HostListener, Renderer2, ViewChild } from '@angular/core'; import { Router } from '@angular/router'; import { LayoutService } from 'src/app/layout/service/app.layout.service'; import { trigger, state, style, animate, transition } from '@angular/animations'; @Component({ selector: 'app-landing', templateUrl: './landing.component.html', styleUrls:['./landing.component.scss'], }) export class LandingComponent { @ViewChild('s1', { static: true }) section1: ElementRef; isNavbarGray = false; isResponsiveMenuGray: boolean = false; animationState = 'hide'; sections: ElementRef[] = []; constructor(public layoutService: LayoutService, public router: Router,public el: ElementRef,private renderer: Renderer2) { } toggleNavbarColor() { this.isNavbarGray = true; } ngAfterViewInit() { // Populate the sections array with ElementRef references this.sections = [ this.section1.nativeElement, // Add other sections as needed ]; } @HostListener('window:scroll', ['$event']) checkScroll() { this.isNavbarGray = window.scrollY > 100; // Adjust the scroll position threshold const scrollPosition = window.pageYOffset || document.documentElement.scrollTop || document.body.scrollTop || 0; // Iterate through sections and apply animation classes this.sections.forEach((section, index) => { const offset = section.nativeElement.offsetTop; const threshold = offset - window.innerHeight * 0.8; // Adjust the threshold as needed // Toggle animation classes based on scroll position if (scrollPosition > threshold) { this.renderer.addClass(section.nativeElement, 'animate-fade-down'); this.renderer.addClass(section.nativeElement, 'animate-fade-down'); // Add other animation classes as needed } else { this.renderer.removeClass(section.nativeElement, 'animate__animated'); this.renderer.removeClass(section.nativeElement, 'animate__fadeInUp'); // Remove other animation classes as needed } }); } }
